14:38.140 --> 14:40.470
Your son is telling
very interesting stories.

14:40.670 --> 14:42.730
And we've got plenty of time.

14:42.930 --> 14:44.860
Dad, are you gonna
have waffles too?

14:47.070 --> 14:49.200
[Miles] Waffles?

14:49.390 --> 14:50.740
Yeah, well,
if I'm gonna have waffles,

14:50.940 --> 14:52.290
we gotta have waffles
the way I made them

14:52.480 --> 14:54.270
when I was growing up,
all right?

14:54.460 --> 14:56.400
In order to do that,
I need two waffles.

14:56.600 --> 14:57.490
Hit me.

14:57.690 --> 14:59.100
First thing we're gonna do,

14:59.300 --> 15:00.710
little bit of peanut butter
on each side.

15:00.910 --> 15:02.580
'Cause we don't want
that jam sogginess

15:02.780 --> 15:04.340
to mess up the delicacy here.

15:04.540 --> 15:06.430
Then gonna put a little bit
of jam just on one side.

15:06.630 --> 15:07.500
We're gonna grab a banana,

15:07.700 --> 15:08.540
put some of those banana slices

15:08.740 --> 15:09.930
all up in the middle.

15:10.130 --> 15:11.260
Then we're gonna take
both sides,

15:11.460 --> 15:12.630
we're gonna
smoosh 'em together.

15:12.830 --> 15:14.020
And then
with chef-like precision,

15:14.220 --> 15:16.370
we're gonna cut
that thing in half.

15:16.570 --> 15:17.700
Sha-blow.

15:17.900 --> 15:20.840
Breakfast PB and J...
for lunch.

15:21.030 --> 15:22.880
- What say you to that?
- [giggles]

15:23.080 --> 15:24.380
I-I want one.

15:24.580 --> 15:25.970
[Rainey] Hey, Nancy.

15:26.170 --> 15:28.080
Sorry. Sorry.

15:28.280 --> 15:31.280
Mine are sitting
right by the door, I know it.

15:31.480 --> 15:33.570
It's okay.
What are neighbor's for?

15:33.760 --> 15:35.090
Doesn't Trish have a key?

15:35.290 --> 15:36.460
Yeah, it's too embarrassing
to call her.

15:36.660 --> 15:38.050
Thank you.

15:38.250 --> 15:40.050
Oh, there's no reason
to be embarrassed.

15:40.250 --> 15:42.290
I lock myself out too,
plenty of times.

15:42.490 --> 15:44.180
It's not necessarily dementia.

15:44.380 --> 15:45.660
- Okay, don't say it.
- Okay.

15:45.860 --> 15:46.820
You don't have to say the word.

15:47.020 --> 15:48.780
Sorry. Sorry.

15:48.980 --> 15:50.580
The D word.

15:50.780 --> 15:52.450
Why don't you walk
with me for a while

15:52.650 --> 15:54.320
till my date picks me up?

15:56.580 --> 15:59.900
You know,
I get flustered and forgetful

16:00.100 --> 16:01.700
when something is
really bothering me.

16:01.900 --> 16:03.380
Is there anything--

16:03.580 --> 16:04.990
Ashley won't let me come
with them to family visitation

16:05.190 --> 16:07.120
to spend the weekend
with my own fucking kid.

16:07.320 --> 16:09.470
Well, that came right out.

16:09.670 --> 16:11.300
And she knows about the D-word.

16:11.500 --> 16:13.580
[Nancy] Well, you need to sit
her ass down and be like,

16:13.780 --> 16:16.500
"Little girl, I'm coming
to the next visitation."

16:16.700 --> 16:18.090
And just sign yourself up.

16:18.290 --> 16:19.590
She is not in charge.

16:19.790 --> 16:21.770
Yeah, but she is, though.

16:21.960 --> 16:23.620
To her,
I'm just crazy old Maurice.

16:23.810 --> 16:25.470
- Bonjour!
- Bonjour!

16:25.660 --> 16:26.660
- [laughs]
- Whoa.

16:26.860 --> 16:28.920
- Whoa.
- Oh.

16:29.120 --> 16:31.470
You okay?

16:31.670 --> 16:33.930
[Rainey] Yes.
[clears throat]

16:34.130 --> 16:35.450
Yes, I'm fine.

16:35.650 --> 16:37.130
Okay. No, no.
You need to sit down.

16:37.330 --> 16:38.410
- Come on.
- [sighs]

16:38.610 --> 16:41.310
[light percussive music plays]

16:41.510 --> 16:44.410
♪ ♪

16:50.110 --> 16:53.070
[all gulping]

16:56.940 --> 16:58.520
[all sigh]

16:58.720 --> 17:01.510
[children chattering]

17:03.470 --> 17:05.530
I wish the boys
were five again.

17:05.730 --> 17:09.270
So many great child memories.

17:09.470 --> 17:11.380
Collin ran that maze
so many times.

17:11.580 --> 17:14.080
He peed himself
and just kept on running.

17:14.280 --> 17:17.150
Little nasty-ass boys.

17:17.350 --> 17:18.870
Remember when they took
the sailing classes

17:19.070 --> 17:20.240
over at the boathouse?

17:20.440 --> 17:22.170
I'm still boycotting
that place.

17:22.370 --> 17:24.810
They wouldn't let Trish sign up
for the teen sailing program

17:25.010 --> 17:26.460
'cause they claimed
they caught her

17:26.660 --> 17:28.050
teaching the other girls
how to--

17:28.250 --> 17:29.700
- [chuckles]
- Whatever.

17:29.900 --> 17:31.620
- We can't support that place.
- Oh.

17:31.820 --> 17:34.560
I say this with love,
but y'all are hella stubborn.

17:34.760 --> 17:36.750
Why hold a grudge for a decade?

17:36.950 --> 17:38.060
Someone fucks with you,

17:38.260 --> 17:39.710
it's the only power
you have left.

17:39.910 --> 17:43.060
You can't win a grudge match
with Ashley.

17:43.260 --> 17:46.420
Or prison, or time.

17:46.610 --> 17:50.770
Sometimes it just is
what the fuck it is.

17:50.970 --> 17:52.920
And you gotta get right
with that.

17:53.120 --> 17:55.770
[dramatic guitar music plays]

17:55.970 --> 17:58.880
♪ ♪

18:00.490 --> 18:02.800
[Miles] <i>All right,</i>
<i>you handsome scoundrel,</i>

18:03.000 --> 18:07.260
this town ain't big enough
for no yellow-bellied bandito.

18:07.460 --> 18:08.720
<i>And I'm the quickest draw</i>

18:08.920 --> 18:10.180
<i>this side</i>
<i>of the Sierra mountains.</i>

18:10.380 --> 18:13.050
Now you put those pistols down!

18:13.250 --> 18:14.600
Never!

18:14.800 --> 18:17.230
- Fine! Blaow!
- [gunshots ringing]

18:17.430 --> 18:20.110
[all mimicking gunshots]

18:22.160 --> 18:25.290
[alarm blaring]

18:27.690 --> 18:29.370
Pause, everyone.

18:29.570 --> 18:31.740
Count. Just the count.
[grunts]

18:31.940 --> 18:33.170
Time out, family.

18:37.480 --> 18:40.490
[Ashley] <i>Hey, Sean,</i>
<i>you want some cookies?</i>

18:40.690 --> 18:45.280
Can we have... ice cream?

18:45.480 --> 18:46.760
[Ashley] <i>I'm sorry, baby.</i>

18:46.960 --> 18:48.500
We're not allowed
to have that in here.

18:48.700 --> 18:51.500
Wow, this place <i>is</i>busted.

18:51.700 --> 18:53.130
[Miles] <i>Hey, enough chitchat.</i>

18:53.330 --> 18:54.900
<i>Now, I got five</i>
<i>in the chamber.</i>

18:55.100 --> 18:58.140
And I aim to use 'em.
One, two, three, four, five.

18:58.340 --> 19:00.580
It's time
for the final showdown!

19:00.780 --> 19:02.060
Ahh!

19:02.260 --> 19:04.600
[yelling]

19:04.800 --> 19:07.890
- [gunshots]
- [both mimicking gunfire]

19:08.090 --> 19:09.130
[Miles] Come on!

19:09.330 --> 19:10.850
Oh! Oh!

19:11.050 --> 19:12.110
[grunting]

19:12.310 --> 19:14.090
- Blaow!
- Oh, no!

19:14.290 --> 19:15.610
Fake-out. Oh.

19:15.810 --> 19:16.420
[Sean] Blaow!

19:16.620 --> 19:18.260
Pow.

19:19.740 --> 19:21.750
[laughs]

19:21.950 --> 19:25.710
But the boy was
a zombie cowboy!

19:25.910 --> 19:27.040
[Ashley]
<i>Not zombie cowboys!</i>

19:27.240 --> 19:30.580
[all yelling]

19:30.780 --> 19:32.740
- Zombie cowboy!
- [screaming]

19:32.940 --> 19:35.390
- [Miles] I'm alive again!
- [Sean] Zombie!

19:35.590 --> 19:37.410
[all yelling]

19:39.980 --> 19:41.940
Good night, baby.

19:42.140 --> 19:43.330
Night, kid.

19:46.810 --> 19:50.500
I'm still thinking about
that word you said I can't say.

19:50.700 --> 19:52.040
<i>Like, why?</i>

19:52.240 --> 19:54.670
<i>Why is it so bad?</i>

19:54.870 --> 19:56.780
There's plenty
of other bad words.

19:56.980 --> 19:58.370
- [Miles] <i>Mm-hmm.</i>
- Why is it badder than f--

19:58.570 --> 19:59.430
You better not.

20:01.430 --> 20:02.550
Fudge?

20:02.750 --> 20:05.310
[laughs]
Well played, sir.

20:10.010 --> 20:11.100
Okay. Um...

20:11.300 --> 20:13.060
[soft music plays]

20:13.260 --> 20:14.650
We are going to tell you

20:14.850 --> 20:18.630
a very, very, very long story.

20:18.830 --> 20:21.240
You might not understand
all of it.

20:21.440 --> 20:24.500
<i>But... we're gonna try.</i>

20:31.940 --> 20:34.800
[somber music plays]

20:35.000 --> 20:37.820
♪ ♪

20:46.350 --> 20:49.900
[laughing]

20:50.100 --> 20:52.790
♪ ♪

21:01.880 --> 21:04.480
[auctioneer shouting
indistinctly]

21:04.680 --> 21:07.540
♪ ♪

21:30.300 --> 21:32.860
[muffled laughter, chatter]

21:33.060 --> 21:35.920
♪ ♪

21:51.890 --> 21:53.100
Sold!

21:53.300 --> 21:56.160
♪ ♪

22:09.040 --> 22:11.640
[muffled laughter, cheering]

22:11.840 --> 22:14.740
♪ ♪

22:16.350 --> 22:17.840
[policeman shouts]

22:18.040 --> 22:20.820
[sirens wailing]

22:21.020 --> 22:23.840
♪ ♪

22:26.580 --> 22:30.200
[shouting]

22:30.400 --> 22:33.090
[music intensifying]

22:33.290 --> 22:36.110
♪ ♪

22:40.810 --> 22:42.320
No!

22:42.520 --> 22:44.580
- [distant gunshots ring]
- [all shouting]

22:44.780 --> 22:47.640
♪ ♪

23:49.050 --> 23:52.970
So your people did that
to my people?

23:55.410 --> 23:57.720
[sighs]

23:57.920 --> 24:00.310
Um...

24:00.510 --> 24:03.840
I am your people, man.

24:04.040 --> 24:06.560
<i>I always will be.</i>

24:06.760 --> 24:09.430
You are my people too.

24:09.630 --> 24:12.910
But it is complicated.

24:13.110 --> 24:17.560
So till it makes
a little bit more sense...

24:20.000 --> 24:23.830
...you can't use that word,
okay?

24:24.030 --> 24:26.920
It's like Voldemort.

24:27.120 --> 24:29.930
Oh!

24:30.130 --> 24:32.170
[both laugh]

24:32.370 --> 24:33.800
[Miles] Hit me.

24:34.000 --> 24:35.410
My man, give me a hug.

24:35.610 --> 24:37.010
Ooh!

24:39.880 --> 24:40.850
I love you.

24:41.050 --> 24:42.000
Love you too, Dad.

24:42.200 --> 24:43.420
Go to sleep.

24:43.620 --> 24:44.890
We'll talk about this
more later.

24:47.670 --> 24:49.140
"It's like Voldemort?"
Really? Okay.

24:49.340 --> 24:51.210
- Well, it worked, didn't it?
- Baby, come on.

24:51.410 --> 24:52.590
Get out of here
before he does something else.

25:00.770 --> 25:03.390
[door creaks]

25:07.780 --> 25:09.040
Earl?

25:10.830 --> 25:13.060
Rainey?

25:13.260 --> 25:15.970
- Is this how you know Nancy?
- Eh...

25:16.170 --> 25:18.560
Everybody's at this
fucking church but me.

25:18.760 --> 25:20.460
- Well, I don't think--
- Let me ask you something.

25:20.660 --> 25:22.000
Do you consider this
a Black church?

25:22.200 --> 25:23.460
It's a very Black church.

25:23.660 --> 25:24.850
- It's hella Black.
- I know.

25:25.050 --> 25:26.030
But it's not--
it's not my shit, though.

25:26.230 --> 25:27.480
I just deliver trays here.

25:27.680 --> 25:28.920
The pastor,
he orders food from me

25:29.120 --> 25:30.810
for, like, events and stuff.

25:31.010 --> 25:33.250
And I just say a prayer on
my way out the door to myself

25:33.450 --> 25:34.860
so I don't feel terrible
about the in-and-out.

25:35.060 --> 25:37.890
So no God for you either?

25:38.090 --> 25:40.480
This is my theory.

25:40.680 --> 25:43.300
God...

25:43.500 --> 25:46.330
God is like the N word to me.

25:46.530 --> 25:49.590
Both were given to us unwanted,
reclaimed, reappropriated,

25:49.790 --> 25:51.880
and now they're whatever
Black people need 'em to be.

25:52.080 --> 25:53.750
So you do pray on the way out?

25:53.950 --> 25:55.640
Well, my kind of prayer, yeah.

25:55.840 --> 25:58.540
I just say what's on my mind.

25:58.740 --> 26:00.840
And as long
as I'm honest about it,

26:01.040 --> 26:04.170
then I feel like I'm giving
an adequate amount of faith.

26:04.370 --> 26:05.880
Doesn't sound
entirely terrible.

26:08.190 --> 26:09.930
I'm walking your way.
Wanna come?

26:11.760 --> 26:13.990
No, I'm just gonna have a seat
for a few minutes.

26:14.190 --> 26:16.510
[Earl] Okay.

26:16.710 --> 26:18.070
Later, Rainey.

26:19.810 --> 26:22.640
[low rumbling building]

26:27.600 --> 26:28.910
[rumbling stops abruptly]

26:33.820 --> 26:35.130
[sighs]

26:39.700 --> 26:42.100
Hello.

26:42.300 --> 26:43.580
I'm me.

26:43.780 --> 26:47.620
I will suppose a you,
I suppose.

26:52.280 --> 26:56.110
I think I am... hitting a wall.

26:57.720 --> 27:00.720
Or boiling over
or spilling out.

27:03.550 --> 27:07.780
It's gotten heavy
is what I mean,

27:07.980 --> 27:10.780
this relentless dread
of uncertainty

27:10.980 --> 27:12.600
draped like a cape.

27:14.870 --> 27:17.790
I can smell the metal
and bleach still

27:17.990 --> 27:22.320
from the floors
where blood and spit

27:22.520 --> 27:24.470
and love and death fall,

27:24.670 --> 27:27.760
and my son is behind
the looking glass there.

27:27.960 --> 27:29.190
[soft dramatic music plays]

27:29.390 --> 27:30.930
I am a vagabond

27:31.130 --> 27:33.460
of hollowed wisdom
I can't share

27:33.660 --> 27:36.590
and a growing anger
I can't bear.

27:36.790 --> 27:38.940
All the many who's, you know?

27:39.140 --> 27:43.160
Who puts a mother's heart
behind a jagged wire?

27:43.360 --> 27:47.410
Who traps memories
in the desert heat?

27:47.610 --> 27:50.000
What might evaporate
before I get him back

27:50.200 --> 27:52.770
laughing in our kitchen seats?

27:55.650 --> 27:59.790
What can I feed an anger
enough of to make it weak?

27:59.990 --> 28:03.270
What truth
to this powerful powerlessness

28:03.470 --> 28:05.580
can I speak?

28:05.780 --> 28:07.920
Because it has made me weak.

28:09.440 --> 28:12.170
I feel angry

28:12.370 --> 28:16.130
at this... weak.

28:16.330 --> 28:19.150
♪ ♪

28:27.290 --> 28:30.110
[indistinct chatter on TV]

28:33.470 --> 28:35.780
[Ashley] I just checked on him.

28:35.980 --> 28:37.480
He's out.

28:37.680 --> 28:38.650
<i>Out</i>out?

28:38.850 --> 28:40.220
Mm-hmm.

28:40.420 --> 28:42.830
[Miles] Shit. Come here.

28:43.030 --> 28:44.770
- Let me get this.
- [Ashley] Oh.

28:44.970 --> 28:47.030
[Miles] Shield children's eyes.

28:47.230 --> 28:49.400
Mm-hmm. Some of that.

28:49.600 --> 28:50.970
Okay, okay, take-take this off.

28:51.170 --> 28:52.470
Okay.

28:52.670 --> 28:54.780
- Oh, ow!
- Shit. Sorry, sorry.

28:54.980 --> 28:56.000
Sorry, sorry,
sorry, sorry, sorry.

28:56.200 --> 28:58.460
Okay, okay.

28:58.660 --> 28:59.940
Oh.

29:00.140 --> 29:02.330
Let's see,
let me get my pants--

29:02.530 --> 29:04.640
oh, shit, this drawstring's
real tight.

29:04.840 --> 29:05.940
- [Ashley] TV up.
- [TV chatter grows]

29:06.140 --> 29:07.640
- Okay.
- [sighs]

29:07.840 --> 29:10.630
[both breathing heavily]

29:17.420 --> 29:20.250
[both whispering indistinctly]

29:21.340 --> 29:22.500
Okay.

29:22.700 --> 29:25.420
[soft music plays]

29:25.620 --> 29:28.220
♪ ♪

29:31.180 --> 29:32.900
God damn.

29:33.100 --> 29:34.540
God damn boy, yo' mom fine!

29:34.740 --> 29:36.470
- Shh!
- [laughs]

29:36.670 --> 29:39.490
♪ ♪

29:40.920 --> 29:43.800
[both breathing heavily]

29:52.370 --> 29:53.550
[whispering]
I love you.

29:54.760 --> 29:56.290
[whispering]
I love you.

30:06.730 --> 30:09.220
Oh, shit.

30:09.420 --> 30:12.330
[moaning]

30:12.530 --> 30:15.350
♪ ♪

30:30.710 --> 30:33.250
Okay, let's go to sleep now
so I can be in a deep sleep

30:33.450 --> 30:35.230
before the "bzzt"
at midnight, please.

30:35.430 --> 30:36.640
Nah, come on.

30:36.840 --> 30:38.340
I made coffee.

30:38.540 --> 30:40.250
I got all of Sean's snacks
out here.

30:40.450 --> 30:43.650
We can just stay up
and eat 'em all.

30:43.850 --> 30:44.850
Come on, stay up with me.

30:45.040 --> 30:46.170
It's our last night.

30:46.370 --> 30:48.200
Baby, I can't. I'm exhausted.

30:48.400 --> 30:50.000
I have to go to work tomorrow.

30:50.200 --> 30:52.440
Okay, well, if the buzzer's
gonna keep you up anyway,

30:52.640 --> 30:54.830
what's one tired night
every three months

30:55.030 --> 30:56.620
so we get
a little bit more time?

30:56.820 --> 30:58.970
Come on, just have
coffee with me, eh?

30:59.170 --> 31:00.320
- Come on.
- [Ashley laughs]

31:00.520 --> 31:02.190
Baby, I don't wanna
have coffee.

31:02.390 --> 31:04.710
It's gonna make it impossible
for me to go to sleep.

31:04.910 --> 31:07.000
Let's just lay in bed together.

31:07.200 --> 31:08.370
[Miles] <i>I don't want to lay.</i>

31:08.570 --> 31:09.500
I did that last night,
all right?

31:09.700 --> 31:11.200
I overslept.

31:11.400 --> 31:12.790
I want to spend some time
with you and me, just us.

31:12.990 --> 31:14.070
<i>He's asleep.</i>

31:14.270 --> 31:16.380
Can we hang out, please?

31:16.580 --> 31:18.900
My eyes are
half-closed already.

31:19.100 --> 31:21.600
It's my sex ritual,
sex and sleep.

31:21.800 --> 31:23.990
Are you gonna make me
fucking beg you right now?

31:24.190 --> 31:25.860
Miles, chill.

31:26.060 --> 31:28.480
Okay, we can just wake up
early tomorrow morning.

31:28.680 --> 31:31.150
Don't tell me to fucking chill.

31:31.350 --> 31:33.420
Don't tell me to fucking chill
in here, all right?

31:33.610 --> 31:34.610
We don't have tomorrow.

31:34.810 --> 31:36.400
You go to work,
and I stay here.

31:36.600 --> 31:38.050
We don't have tomorrow, okay?

31:38.250 --> 31:39.880
- This is almost over!
- Miles, lower your voice.

31:40.080 --> 31:42.880
[alarm blaring]

31:43.080 --> 31:45.860
[tense music plays]

31:46.060 --> 31:48.920
♪ ♪

32:57.430 --> 32:58.430
[knock on door]

32:59.470 --> 33:02.440
You hiding out up here?

33:02.640 --> 33:05.270
Uh, I got home from work.

33:05.470 --> 33:06.920
Just been laying here.

33:07.120 --> 33:09.750
Well, I'm playing bones
with Sean,

33:09.950 --> 33:12.010
who keeps saying
he's playing Dad rules,

33:12.210 --> 33:13.150
so I don't get a turn.

33:13.340 --> 33:15.170
I need a break.

33:15.370 --> 33:16.750
I brought you some tea.

33:18.970 --> 33:21.200
Yeah, I know he's a handful
right now, I get it.

33:21.400 --> 33:25.850
No, I'm glad you guys had
a great family weekend.

33:26.050 --> 33:27.500
I'm happy you're both back.

33:29.280 --> 33:30.760
It's a big house.

33:33.550 --> 33:35.070
[Ashley] <i>Thanks, Rainey.</i>

33:38.250 --> 33:41.570
We did have a happy weekend.

33:41.760 --> 33:42.940
You're welcome.

33:43.140 --> 33:44.120
Good.

33:45.080 --> 33:46.520
What's that?

33:47.780 --> 33:50.420
